===Pronunciation===
* ''[[RP]] & US:'' {{AHD|rīt}}, {{IPA|/raɪt/}}, {{SAMPA|/raIt/}}
*: '''Homophones''': [[right]], [[rite]], [[wright]]
*: [[Rhymes:English:-aɪt|Rhymes: -aɪt]]

===Verb===
{{en-verb2|'''to write'''|'''[[writes]]'''|'''[[wrote]] '''or, archaic,''' [[writ]]'''|'''[[written]] '''or, archaic,''' [[writ]]'''|'''[[writing]]'''}}

# {{transitive}} To form (letters, words or symbols) on a surface in order to communicate.
#: ''The pupil wrote his name on the paper.'' 
# {{transitive}} To be the author of (a book, article, poem, etc.).
#: ''My uncle writes newspaper articles for The Herald.'' 
# {{transitive}} {{US}} To send a letter to. 
#: ''Please write me when you get there.''
# {{intransitive}} To form letters, etc., in order to communicate.
#: ''He's been '''writing''' on the wall.''
# {{intransitive}} To be an author.
#: ''I '''write''' for a living.''

